      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">On a laboratory scale oxygen can be prepared by heating potassium manganate(VII)  </text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">– KMn</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">O</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">4</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">, or potassium chlorate(V) – KCl</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">O</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">3</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0"> with manganese(IV) oxide – Mn</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">O</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">2</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">. The industrial preparation involves the fractional distillation of liquefied air. Not only oxygen, but also nitrogen and argon are obtained by this process. Oxygen can also be produced in small quantities by the electrolysis of water.</text>
   </par>
